@wezzynl Unfortunately the Implicit Grant Flow requires a whitelist of all valid `redirect_url`s. Basically this would mean for every user I would need to add their IP address or domain to the Spotify App's whitelist. While this was fine when it was just a small project that only I was using, it's really viable now.

Basically the off-site request goes to a public domain (which is whitelisted) and generates an `access_token` and `refresh_token`, which are then passed back to Spotmop.

Feel free to tinker and see if you can find a way to make this work though - the Spotify authentication is the slightly more cumbersome area that would be nice to simplify.

Yes, you can. You can write a rule to start a ruleset or you can have a top level branch rule:

```python
with statechart('risk3'):
    with state('start'):
        @when_all(m.type == 'A')
        @to('A')
        def action_A(c):

        @when_all(m.type == 'B')
        @to('B')
        def action_B(c):
            
    with state('A'):
        # do your thing

    with state('B'):
        # do your thing

run_all()
```

Please take a look at the docs for all the details:

https://github.com/jruizgit/rules/blob/master/docs/py/reference.md

Looks like the events are being filtered out because hangups doesn't set a `client_id` in the request headers. The filtering is removed when it's set to any of the recognized values.

