Hi @ecz4!

The internal natural sort algorithm uses chunking to sort a mixture of text and numbers, it does ignore leading zeros. So, if you want to use the built-in JavaScript sorting method, which should behave as you need, then set the [`textSorter` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#textsorter) for that column to use a basic sort method as follows ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/bbxxomhx/1515/)):

```js
$(function() {
  $('table').tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    textSorter: {
    	0: function(a, b) {
	    	return a > b ? 1 : (a < b ? -1 : 0);
      }
    }
  });
});
```

On the doc page, you can look under the [`headers` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#headers), which has will redirect you to the [`config.parsers`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#parsers) entry... it should be more obvious, so I'll add a new "built-in parsers" demo with a full list.

