I've looked at finding the right file and do not think there is a remotely accurate way to do so. The problem is that "the file name" is several layers down the stack but the number of layers varies. The unit tests are probably the easiest cases since they only involve individual files for Migrate, jQuery, and the unit tests. It only gets more complicated with combined files, plugins, async code such as ajax, or event handlers that are called back from within jQuery. Unreliable information here would be worse than just leaving the stack trace.

If someone would like to continue experimenting with this, add the following code [after the warning message output](https://github.com/jquery/jquery-migrate/blob/dfc7de9d09a5975773715b1d46e4f199bd1ffa5d/src/migrate.js#L52):

```js
			try {
